	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I think i have figured out my problem. The plate in the back isn't an RF shield like I thought it was. It is a heat sink. It makes all makes sense. Even the AV Famicom has one and that doesn't have a RF output. Once I put it back on, it has run great for 15 hours in a stress test.  Just got to check on it when I get home from work.
<br />
<br />I originally took it off because I needed room for the AV jacks. Now I can make a minor cut out to it to allow it to fit together correctly.
<br />
<br />Just wanted to post this in case it might help somebody.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


