	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><img src="http://www.fileden.com/files/2008/4/21/1876835//VideoBuffer.png" alt="Image" />
<br />
<br />Cut off PPU video signal output from the rest of the NES and feed it into the input of the buffer. Output signal can be fed to any TV and should work nicely. I used 56ohm resistor on the output to get the brightness down.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
